{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"eb5f108b-a66b-47dc-802d-378e76caf98f","content":"Here's the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- \\\n  --treenode-filter \"/**/[Category=Integration]\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\nEverything after `--` is forwarded to the new test platform. Key changes:\n\n| VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|\n| `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` | `--treenode-filter \"/**/[Category=Integration]\"` |\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang --blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n**Required NuGet packages** (add to your test projects):\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump\" />\n```\n\n**Project file settings** (needed for .NET 8):\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nThis property enables `dotnet test` to forward to the new platform runner. Without it, `dotnet test` falls back to VSTest and ignores the `--` arguments.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9400a914-8a21-4f90-9db1-7e579041f988","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing tooling migration, not a codebase task.\n\nLet me provide the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n\nKey differences:\n- `dotnet test` still works but the underlying runner changes\n- Filter syntax changes from `--filter` to `--filter` (but the platform uses `--treenode-filter` or keeps `--filter` depending on configuration)\n- Logger changes from `--logger trx` to `--report-trx`\n\n\n- Code coverage and blame options also shift with the new platform\n\nWhen using `dotnet test` as the entry point with Microsoft.Testing.Platform, many options pass through, though the syntax differs when running the test executable directly. The filter syntax remains largely compatible through `dotnet test`, but the TRX reporting now uses `--report-trx` instead of the logger approach. To use these features with Microsoft.Testing.Platform, I need to add specific NuGet packages: `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` for TRX logging, `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` for code coverage, and the crash/hang dump packages. The command structure changes to forward arguments after `--` to the test host, using flags like `--report-trx`, `--hang-dump`, and `--crashdump` instead of the VSTest equivalents.\n\nFor .NET 8 projects, I'd need to enable the testing platform integration in the project file, and then the filter syntax shifts from `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` to `--treenode-filter` format, while code coverage moves from `--collect` to `--coverage` with format options.\n\nThe remaining blame-related flags map to crash and hang dump options with their respective packages, and I can run this either through `dotnet test` with the arguments passed after `--`, or directly invoke the test executable with the same parameters.","outputTokens":1658,"requestId":"2863:101CE8:16A94E9:180D78D:6A046010"},"id":"1d637391-a05f-4237-ae0c-eed600d80237","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:27:40.499Z","parentId":"d1b89e48-df6d-4ca2-bbaf-8cc029d394c7"}
